Wow, this game is amazing! It's one of those rare children's games that actually respects their intellect and has some trully ingenious puzzles that test your deduction skills. There are only 12 puzzles in the game, however they are incredibly well designed and each has 4 levels of difficulty which require different strategies to finish, so the game doesn't feel starved for content. It's evident that the game's focused on being both fun to play and a great logic exercise, and it shines for it!

This brings back so many memories! However, so far at least one of the 
levels are broken on hardest difficulty. If you want a perfect run, you 
need a lot of luck and patience, as you will be restarting one level a lot 
by closing and reopening the app because of a glitch in game coding. In the 
mirrors you'll get a situation where they don't give you more than one 
fixated eye change option and both sides have two sets of unique eyes (one 
Zoombini is doomed). Another one is, no matter which side, a flexible 
feature will change on you in the second user round, so they no longer 
match and your Zoombini falls. It's extremely frustrating.

Will always and forever love this game, so glad it's been revamped and 
brought back!

I played this game when it first came out on pc waaay back in the day. It 
was my favorite game, and I played for hours on end. It became a huge part 
of my childhood. Nothing has changed. It is still as fun as it was all 
those years ago, and I'm only a bit better at the puzzles now. This was 
such an obscure game that I was certain that it would be one of those joys 
lost to the fog of time, and I was elated when I heard it had been revived 
for a new era. If you're a fan of logic puzzles, adventure, and need 
something more involved than a matching game to play, do not miss out on 
this timeless classic.

Every time I tried to download/install it I got error code 905, so I've never actually been able to install it... anyone have a solution to this? Too late for a refund. I'd love to try this game... any suggestions?
replyContent:
Hello Drinkaren, 
Looks like that's an issue with the Google Play app. Try these steps:  
Go to the Settings menu on your Android device
Go to Applications
Select "Manage Applications" or "Application Manager"
Select "Google Play Store". If you do not see it check the "All" tab.
Select "Uninstall Updates"
Restart device & launch Play store

This was by and far one of my favorite games of all time.  I played it for years as a kid, and got the re-release now for myself and my children. It's one of those rare educational games that manages to be a good and enjoyable game, while being really good at teaching the subject it set out to teach.  I really can't express the happiness I felt, getting to play through this last night with my wife, after Years of not having it being able to work on my computer. We played through the first 7 puzzles (Got to the second campfire) with i group, and she seemed impressed.  I'll be honest, while it isn't hard math or reading skills, the lessons this game teaches to children are super important. The recognition of logic isn't something you can really quiz people on without these kinds of puzzles, and having a firm foundation here can really help people with a Lot of other skills.  I Often recommend this game to people and will do so to every parent I know.  Thank you Again to Terc for redoing this for a new generation.

I donated to TERC's kickstarter when it went live and I'm thrilled to finally see this released.  This game was a huge part of my childhood and the team has really done a fantastic job of faithfully recreating every aspect of the game.     As for the game itself, this is not your traditional boring educational game.  It is pretty creative in the way it presents its puzzles and makes logic really fun.  The music is also fantastic and I'm really glad they kept all the original voice work and soundtrack.  So far I've played two full games and haven't encountered any bugs or strange mishaps which is really nice.     My only major complaint I have about the game is that sometimes I'll accidentally press the continue on button while I"m still getting the Zoombinis across the puzzle and the game just moves on to the next level leaving the remaining Zoombinis behind.  It would be nice to have a confirmation button that asks if you are sure you want to move on to the next level even though you still have more Zoombinis to get through.     All in all this is game is a classic and seeing it come back to life after almost two decades is amazing.
